text.tspan: “I wish I could buy fresg goods meanwhile spend less time at supermarket”
Teddie is a software engineer and he rents a studio near
his office in because engineers have to work in shifts
including night shifts. There’s no many restaurants near his
office so he usually makes meal at home. Teddie goes
to supermarkets once a week. Apparently, he doesn’t need
much food since he lives by himself.
Moreover, Teddie has started to live by himself recently and he
doesn’t know too much about fresh goods which his parents
help him to prepare in the past. He always feels confused about
how to choice fresh and in season goods.
Sometimes, Teddie has to travel to other cities to visit clients
or attend meetings so he has a uncertain schedule. Although
he enjoys going to farmers’ market, he usually has a conflict
with the schedule of farmers’ market. Thus, he always looks for
a more flexible and efficient way to buy fresh and in season
• Have a healthy body for work
• Spend minimal time at supermarket shopping
• Have a well balance between work and life
• Unsure which vegetables or fruits are
• Unsure the food is fresh or not
